<section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Dragon (<span class="chinese-char">龍</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Chen (辰)</strong>, carrying Yang Earth energy with hidden Water and Wood. In the 2026 Fire Horse year, the Dragon benefits from the <strong>generating cycle</strong> — Fire produces Earth, directly strengthening the Dragon's core element.</p>
      <p>The Dragon-Horse relationship is <strong>naturally harmonious</strong>. Both are Yang, action-oriented signs that respect strength and vision. The Horse's Fire energy fuels the Dragon's ambitious Earth nature, creating conditions for expansion and influence. This is a year where the Dragon's natural magnetism operates at full power.</p>
      <p>The Dragon also serves as a <strong>storage branch</strong> for Water energy (辰 contains hidden 癸 Water), which helps moderate Fire's intensity. This internal balance gives the Dragon an advantage over other Earth signs — the Dragon can absorb Fire's energy without becoming overheated or rigid.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>Career prospects for the Dragon in 2026 are <strong>exceptionally strong</strong>. Fire's productive energy feeds the Dragon's ambition, creating momentum for leadership positions, business expansion, and public recognition. The Dragon's authority is respected, and institutional support is available for large-scale projects.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> benefits from Earth's strengthened position. Investment in property, infrastructure, and established businesses yields returns. The Dragon should leverage the year's productive energy for long-term asset building rather than speculative gains.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Real estate, construction, government, military, large-scale enterprise, mining, and any field requiring vision and authoritative leadership.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>Fire's warmth adds <strong>generosity and expressiveness</strong> to the Dragon's love life. The Dragon's partner benefits from increased attention and grand romantic gestures. However, the Dragon's heightened ambition can create competition between career and relationship priorities — conscious scheduling of quality time prevents drift.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Dragons</strong> attract admirers through demonstrated success and confident energy. Romantic connections formed through professional or social leadership contexts have the strongest foundation. The Monkey month (August) and Rat month (December) — the Dragon's San He allies — are most favourable for meaningful connections.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>Excess Earth from Fire's generating cycle can manifest as <strong>digestive heaviness, muscle tension, and overthinking</strong>. The Dragon's physical constitution is robust, but the tendency to absorb responsibility can create chronic stress patterns.</p>
      <p><strong>Stomach and spleen health</strong> require attention. The Dragon should avoid heavy, late-night meals and excessive alcohol — both common accompaniments to the Dragon's active social life. Regular physical activity, preferably outdoors, helps circulate stagnant Earth energy.</p>
      <p>Strength training and martial arts suit the Dragon's competitive nature and help channel excess Earth energy productively.</p>
    </section>

